03efa-profile.jpg","avatarPreviewURL":"https:\u002F\u002Fstaging.cohostcdn.org\u002Favatar\u002F28025-9a783854-6a48-4f92-9b91-a099a4203efa-profile.jpg","headerURL":null,"headerPreviewURL":null,"privacy":"public","url":"","pronouns":"any","flags":[],"avatarShape":"squircle","loggedOutPostVisibility":"public","frequentlyUsedTags":[],"askSettings":{"enabled":false,"allowAnon":false,"requireLoggedInAnon":true},"contactCard":[],"deleteAfter":null,"isSelfProject":null}},{"comment":{"commentId":"1f2aae4b-68ff-420c-a1d6-248c0dd29674","postedAtISO":"2024-09-11T00:28:11.733Z","deleted":false,"body":"I'm sad to see the site go, really. But, between, staff paying themselves 94k USD a year per person ( https:\u002F\u002Fusesthis.com\u002Finterviews\u002Fjae.kaplan\u002F ) and not accepting volunteers, I saw this coming from miles away years ago. You've not really done anything to make the site sustainable, and you've not been very responsible with your financials, if I'm gonna judge by the interview promoting the site talking how you paid yourselves payed yourselves *obscene* salaries from your rich friend's loan, chatting about your $1200 desk chair and other $300 chair that holds your $400 controller.\n\nI may sound harsh here, but I do it out of love for what you've created, and a severe sadness about how it turned out: I hope you don't get it in your heads that this happened because of capitalism being shit. It is shit, don't get me wrong, but this site isn't going down because it was \"too good for this world\". You did it to yourselves. Internalize that, and your next project will go better (and I'll be there, all too happy to put my foot in my mouth).","children":[{"comment":{"commentId":"7bb18f0c-d101-4167-a985-d9cd60072dc2","postedAtISO":"2024-09-12T03:45:28.542Z","deleted":false,"body":"Part of the concept was that it would pay competitive with Big Tech. Roughly $100k\u002Fyr\u002Fperson (what they should be at now, including COL raises) plus company equity is genuinely starting salary at Google. ","children":[{"comment":{"commentId":"5bbceda4-5600-4174-b3e8-bcf33d1b8d52","postedAtISO":"2024-09-12T03:58:19.147Z","deleted":false,"body":"Okay, sure... But this *isn't* Google. Google is a near-monopoly reigning in billions-with-a-b dollars a year. Cohost is\u002Fwas a small, struggling social media which was actively leaking money. The sentiment is nice, but the simple fact is that they are not the same and it is irresponsible to treat them as such. It's that sort of thinking that put staff into the position they are in now.","children":[{"comment":{"commentId":"a10b1b14-a16d-4b7a-b0a5-594811d9fe7b","postedAtISO":"2024-09-19T04:01:15.127Z","deleted":false,"body":"My tone was apparently unclear. I apologize for that. The comment you replied to wasn't meant to be a defense of Cohost. \n\nGoogle doesn't repeatedly discover that they don't have money to make the next payroll cycle, beg the Adsense clients to donate money to cover it, and not change anything about their business strategy. At some point, if you keep walking into the same wall repeatedly, it's going to fall on you. ","children":[{"comment":{"commentId":"2cb68bfa-2c03-4075-9ae5-228f2b17491d","postedAtISO":"2024-09-20T21:19:20.897Z","deleted":false,"body":"\u003E The day-to-day needs of just running the site meant developing alternative funding options wasn’t possible.\n\u003E \n\u003E MAU and MRR are down across the year. We’ve managed to build a social media platform that many of our users love, but we just don’t have enough users and we don’t have the resources to safely scale up.\n\nI'm going to assume you missed this part.\n","children":[],"postId":7611443,"inReplyTo":"a10b1b14-a16d-4b7a-b0a5-594811d9fe7b","hasCohostPlus":false,"hidden":false},"canInteract":"allowed","canEdit":"not-allowed","canHide":"not-allowed","poster":{"projectId":87711,"handle":"SacchiHikaru","displayName":"Sacchi Hikaru","dek":"Tales of Loss and Fire and Faith","description":"![A Gay of Mild Rele